          <p id="IO-UN.2610">WMO was established in 1950 and was recognized as a specialized agency of the UN in 1951, operating in the fields of meteorology, climatology, operational hydrology and related areas, as well as their applications.</p>
          <int-org-section id="IO-UN.2611" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
               <heading>Members</heading>
               <p id="IO-UN.2612">WMO has 187 member states and six member territories.</p>
          </int-org-section>
     </int-org-block>
     <int-org-section id="IO-UN.2613" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
          <heading>Organization</heading>
          <heading-note>April 2024</heading-note>
          <int-org-section id="IO-UN.2614" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
               <heading>World Meteorological Congress</heading>
               <p id="IO-UN.2615">The Congress is convened every four years and represents all members; it adopts regulations, and determines policy, programme and budget. In October 2021 an Extraordinary WMO Congress was convened, as a virtual event, to address specific strategic priorities. The 19th regular quadrennial Congress was held in late May-early June 2023, in Geneva.</p>
          </int-org-section>
          <int-org-section id="IO-UN.2616" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
               <heading>Executive Council</heading>
               <p id="IO-UN.2617">The Council has 37 members and meets at least once a year to prepare studies and recommendations for the Congress; it supervises the implementation of Congress resolutions and regulations, informs members on technical matters and offers advice. The Council is served by a Policy Advisory Committee.</p>
          </int-org-section>
          <int-org-section id="IO-UN.2618" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
               <heading>Secretariat</heading>
               <p usage="edio">
        The secretariat acts as an administrative, documentary and information centre; undertakes special technical studies; produces publications; organizes meetings of WMO constituent bodies; acts as a link between the meteorological and hydrometeorological services of the world, and provides information for the general public. It comprises a cabinet office, and departments of governance services, services, science and innovation, infrastructure, and member services. It hosts the secretariat of the 
        <xr pageref="N" ref="IO-UNEP.101">Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change</xr>
         (see under UNEP).
      </p>
